        <abstract> 
<p>First impressions of Haeckel’s <hi rend="italic">Generelle morphologie</hi>.</p>  
<p>Has received THH’s [<hi rend="italic">Lessons in elementary</hi>] <hi rend="italic">Physiology</hi> [1866]</p>  
<p>and reread <hi rend="italic">Man’s place</hi>.</p>  
<p>Asks THH to read revised "Hybridism" chapter in new edition of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>. Hopes it will change THH’s view.</p> 
            <p>Convinced of P. S. Pallas’ view of loss of sterility under domestication.</p>
        </abstract>
